@N0040:  draw a vector on all scopes
@N0103:  pilfered from tic tac toe
@N0111:  segment count should be negative, ie, we will incr the value until positive
@N0117:  save the return address
@N0121:  shift from 0-15 axis to -8 to +7
@N0124:  multiply by 128 to get +/- 1024 screen coords, multiply by 64 to get to bit 0
@N0125:  initialize vector gen
@N0127:  shift from 0-31 axis to -16 to +15
@N0131:  multiply by 128 to get +/- 1024 screen coords, multiply by 64 to get to bit 0
@N0132:  Draw a segment with x=ACC
@N0134:  save the return address
@N0136:  shift from 0-15 axis to -8 to +7
@N0137:  multiply by 128 to get +/- 1024 screen coords, multiply by 64 to get to bit 0
@N0140:  initialize vector gen
@N0142:  shift from 0-15 axis to -8 to +7
@N0144:  re-fetch the next x_arg
@N0145:  multiply by 128 to get +/- 1024 screen coords, multiply by 64 to get to bit 0
@N0146:  Draw a segment with x=ACC
@N0150:  increment the segment counter
@N0156:  +32 in the top half of the word
@N0157:  +32 in the bottom half of the word
